One drunk bartender and no one sober watching the place.

"Under the Ontario Liquor License Act, no person shall sell or supply liquor or permit liquor to be sold or supplied to any person who is or appears to be intoxicated. If they do, they will face a fine up to $15,000. License holders also face fines up to $10,000 if they permit drunkenness, unlawful gambling or riotous, quarrelsome, violent or disorderly conduct to occur on the premises, or if they, or the manager appointed by the license holder, fails to maintain control over the premises."